5: Has it already been fifteen years?
10:
I thought you said your hometown
was located here. I don't see
anything.
13:
The dunes shift over time; anything
could be hiding under the sand.
That or the king's troops found this
place first.
16: Either way, my home is gone...
22:
Ah, fudge pops! I swear there are
more golems in this desert than
cactuses!
24:
Look alive, boys! We have to stop
this ancient hunk of rock!
31:
Barrek, no! Oh, wait. He's already got
it handled...
37:
C'mon. There's nothing left for me in
this world now.
43:
It's me! Cas! You remember me,
right? We used to train together!
50:
You're a sight for sore eyes! I
thought we'd seen the last of you
fifteen years ago.
51:
But here you are with the Hellcat of
the Dunes!
53:
I heard from traveling entertainers
that you got into a scuffle down
south. Killed two nobles and all.
55:
Let the past rest. We've got the
present to talk about, don't we?
58:
Heh, my bad. It was the first thing
that came to mind. But the fact that
you've come now, it's like you were
sent from above.
60:
We're on a mission, you see. We've
been charged with assassinating
this domain's lord.
63:
It's finally time to fulfill our dearest
wish. It's what we were raised to do.
64:
After our village was destroyed, it
took us fifteen years to put this plan
together. We won't have a chance
like this again, Barrek!
67:
You couldn't even handle that
golem. How are you going to take
down the lord?
70:
You took care of that dumb
construct before we could make a
move. Here, check out our new team.
72:
Say hello to our newest assassins,
trained specifically for this job. And
they're even better than you, Barrek.
73:
They'll sneak in as musicians and do
the deed while he's sleeping.
77:
Of all the underhanded... You're
going to use kids as assassins?!
82: Barrek, we can't go along with this!
86:
They stay out of it. My answer is
already made up.
89:
And that answer—to your
disappointment, Cas—is that I also
won't be joining you.
92:
But we've waited so long for this
chance. Do you really want to throw
it away?
93:
We're finally strong enough to take
him out! That's why we've survived
all this time!
95:
I didn't train this much to be just a
killer.
103: Where do you think you're going?
107:
I can't take it anymore. I've gotta go
stop those punks.
113:
But you could ask us to come with
you instead of assuming we'll stop
you, you know.
116:
Grrr, then why did you bother
pretending to sleep?
122:
Well, it doesn't look like we'll have to
walk very far to deal with this issue.
128:
Is this how you do things now, Cas?
Killing all your targets in their sleep?
139:
Hah. Guess he saw 'em coming!
C'mon, Alk! Let's get in there!
147:
Why? You're strong enough now... So
why haven't you gotten our revenge
yet?!
149:
There are better uses for strength,
Cas.
152:
Back then, when we were willing to
beat each other to a pulp... There
was no sense in it.
154:
After all this time, why did you take
up the fight again? What did you
think it would prove?
158: I'm done with the senseless killing.
173:
This is a land far, far away from the
desert. If you want to return one day
and get your revenge, then you'll
stay here and survive.
175:
Fight, grow stronger, and survive.
Then you will understand the value
of not only your own lives, but of
those you take, as well.
180:
Call me Barrek. When the time
comes, we'll have our rematch.
